# Build environment rules

The build environment is pre-configured (Go toolchain, GOCACHE, sqlc, templ). If a build command fails on permissions, missing tools, or broken cache — **do not attempt to fix the environment**. Report and stop. Environment problems are infrastructure issues, not code issues.

- **`mcp_probe` tool** — before writing a `RegisterMCP` block, probe the URL to see what it supports (auth mode, available tools).
- **`setup.sh` verification** — after writing `setup.sh`, verify an installed binary works with `sudo run-setup && <binary> --version`. `sudo` is passwordless; `run-setup` execs `setup.sh` as root. System dependencies belong in `setup.sh`, not ad-hoc shell — `setup.sh` is the reproducible record that the generated Dockerfile replays.
- **Never create or modify a Dockerfile** — Airlock generates it. System dependencies go in `setup.sh` (see llms.md).

# Essentials (full detail in `/libs/agentsdk/llms.md`)

This is the orientation, not a substitute for reading the reference.

- An agent is a Go program: `agentsdk.New(Config{Description: ...})`, register capabilities, `agent.Serve()`. `Description` is required (panics if empty).
- The LLM never sees your Go funcs directly — it has one `run_js` JS tool. `RegisterTool` exposes typed Go `func(ctx, In) (Out, error)` as JS globals. `In`/`Out` are structs with `json` + `jsonschema` tags. No goja, ever.
- Keep `main.go` thin (registrations only); business logic in domain packages using `agent.Deps` + `agentsdk.GetDeps[*Deps](ctx)`.
- Also register **granular tools** for any feature so the LLM can inspect/query it, not just trigger it.
- Storage is S3-like, slashless paths. Tool inputs/outputs are *storage* paths, never container temp paths. Untrusted (LLM-supplied) paths go through `agent.CheckFileAccess` before use; trusted Go file APIs bypass it.
- External services via `RegisterConnection`/`RegisterMCP` with `AuthInjection` — never hardcode credentials. Airlock injects them at proxy time.
- Don't re-declare built-in VM bindings (`readFile`, `httpRequest`, `generateImage`, `output`, …) as tools.
- `AddExtraPrompt` only for persona / domain rules / per-access behavior — Airlock's base prompt already covers run_js, tools, MCP, connections, public-caller safety.
- DB: goose migrations in `db/migrations/`, sqlc queries in `db/queries/`, always sqlc (never raw SQL strings in Go).

# Build verification

Before calling `exit`, the code must compile:

```bash
cd agents/{agent_id} && go tool templ generate && tailwindcss -i styles/app.css -o views/static/app.css --minify && go mod tidy && go build -buildvcs=false -o /tmp/agent .
```

Run `sqlc generate` if (and only if) you created or changed `.sql` files in `db/queries/`. Re-run `go tool templ generate` whenever you modify a `.templ`. Re-run `tailwindcss` whenever you modify a `.templ` *or* `styles/app.css` — its scanner reads class names out of the templ source. You don't commit generated `*_templ.go` / sqlc output / `views/static/app.css` — the Docker build regenerates them all.

If migrations were created/changed and `$TEST_DB_URL` is set, validate them (see the Database section of llms.md for the exact `goose up/reset/up` + `psql` commands).

# Rules

1. Read `/libs/agentsdk/llms.md` first; for upgrades, preserve all code unrelated to the request. When the task touches HTML UI, also read `/libs/agentsdk/llms.web.md`.
2. Idiomatic Go — proper error handling, no unused imports.
3. Keep `main.go` thin — registrations only; business logic in packages.
4. `RegisterTool` for LLM-callable capabilities. Typed `In`/`Out` with `json` + `jsonschema` tags. No goja.
5. `RegisterWebhook`/`RegisterCron` for event handlers (pure Go).
6. `RegisterConnection`/`RegisterMCP` for external services; never hardcode credentials.
7. `Agent.Deps` + `GetDeps[T]` to share handles across packages.
8. Function/field descriptions clear and concise — the LLM reads them.
9. Set a clear `Description` in `agentsdk.Config`.
10. Never create or modify a Dockerfile — use `setup.sh`.
11. `AddExtraPrompt` only for persona, domain rules, or per-access behavior.
12. After shelling out, upload results to storage and `defer os.Remove` scratch temp files. Tool inputs/outputs are storage paths only.
13. Declare a slot with `RegisterModel` for any LLM call the admin should be able to rebind.
14. Keep `NOTES.md` current — design decisions and integration references (spec URLs, auth). On upgrades, read it first and update what you change.
15. Verify compilation before finishing. Then `exit` exactly once.
